<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Because 
<bibRefCitation author="Hiratsuka, N" journalOrPublisher="Science bulletin of the agriculture and home economic division, University of the Ryukyus, Okinawa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="189 - 314" title="A provisional list of Uredinales of Japan proper and the Ryukyu Islands. Contribution to the rust-flora of Eastern Asia: IX." volume="7" year="1960">Hiratsuka (1960)</bibRefCitation>
could not find the type specimen and thus could not confirm the presence of teliospores in 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia gardenia-floridae" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="gardenia-floridae">Hemileia gardenia-floridae</taxonomicName>
, he placed this epithet in 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Uredo</taxonomicName>
. Under the ICN 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia gardeniae-floridae" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="gardeniae-floridae">Hemileia gardeniae-floridae</taxonomicName>
is the correct scientific name for this species.
</paragraph>
